WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.871 --> 00:00:06.496
<i>Previously on</i> Marshals...

2
00:00:06.579 --> 00:00:07.996
I don't think
we've seen you on Broken Rock

3
00:00:08.079 --> 00:00:09.621
since Monica's burial.

4
00:00:09.704 --> 00:00:11.288
She picked out her favorite spot
on East Camp for me

5
00:00:11.371 --> 00:00:12.621
- to visit her.
- Grandpa Long wants us to

6
00:00:12.704 --> 00:00:13.663
honor Mom at
the remembrance ceremony.

7
00:00:13.746 --> 00:00:14.746
Asked about borrowing

8
00:00:14.829 --> 00:00:15.954
her favorite necklace.

9
00:00:16.038 --> 00:00:17.204
Chair's empty. if you've

10
00:00:17.288 --> 00:00:18.538
got a minute to chat.

11
00:00:18.621 --> 00:00:19.621
You want more than a minute.

12
00:00:19.704 --> 00:00:21.121
But I don't have that to give.

13
00:00:21.204 --> 00:00:23.663
- Bartender's my kid.
- She's your daughter?

14
00:00:23.746 --> 00:00:25.621
Marshal badge puts you
on the wrong side of me.

15
00:00:25.704 --> 00:00:27.663
That horse is a grenade
with the pin pulled.

16
00:00:27.746 --> 00:00:29.121
That's anger with legs.

17
00:00:29.204 --> 00:00:30.871
I saw Monica's shoes
by the door.

18
00:00:30.954 --> 00:00:33.913
I'm guessing that's her horse
terrorizing your ranch.

19
00:00:49.496 --> 00:00:50.913
Dad!

20
00:00:50.996 --> 00:00:52.579
Tate!

21
00:00:56.579 --> 00:00:58.496
Hey!

22
00:00:58.579 --> 00:01:00.496
Hey!

23
00:01:02.913 --> 00:01:04.829
Hey. hey! Hey!

24
00:01:16.538 --> 00:01:18.746
Ow.

25
00:01:18.829 --> 00:01:21.121
Lucky it was your arm
and not your head.

26
00:01:21.204 --> 00:01:23.954
You know better than
to mess with that mustang.

27
00:01:24.038 --> 00:01:25.996
Thought I could
connect with him.

28
00:01:26.079 --> 00:01:28.121
Thinking is the last thing
you were doing.

29
00:01:30.454 --> 00:01:31.704
He was Mom's.

30
00:01:31.788 --> 00:01:33.079
And he's alive.

31
00:01:35.038 --> 00:01:36.788
I just wanted to feel that.

32
00:01:36.871 --> 00:01:39.413
There's wanting to connect and
there's getting yourself killed.

33
00:01:40.954 --> 00:01:42.746
You don't have to be so angry.

34
00:01:42.829 --> 00:01:44.621
I am angry.

35
00:01:44.704 --> 00:01:48.288
The only way left for this world
to hurt me is through you. son.

36
00:01:51.288 --> 00:01:52.954
Won't happen again.

37
00:01:53.038 --> 00:01:54.579
Damn right.

38
00:01:54.663 --> 00:01:56.788
Stallion's moving on.

39
00:01:56.871 --> 00:01:58.663
He's Mom's.

40
00:01:59.704 --> 00:02:02.246
You can't just
erase every memory of her.

41
00:02:02.329 --> 00:02:04.538
He's caused enough trouble
around here.

42
00:02:04.621 --> 00:02:06.788
It's time for his new beginning.

43
00:02:20.829 --> 00:02:23.329
You sure all that grease
is good at your age?

44
00:02:23.413 --> 00:02:25.538
Need the calories and trying to
get back to my fighting weight.

45
00:02:25.621 --> 00:02:27.579
You're not worried
it might slow you down?

46
00:02:27.663 --> 00:02:29.996
I know how you like to bolt
without a warning.

47
00:02:30.079 --> 00:02:32.913
That's-that's funny.

48
00:02:32.996 --> 00:02:34.579
I mean. it's mean.
but it's funny.

49
00:02:34.663 --> 00:02:37.329
You were always skinny.

50
00:02:37.413 --> 00:02:40.121
You were like a toothpick
in my baby pictures.

51
00:02:41.829 --> 00:02:43.913
Oh. you. uh.
you still have those?

52
00:02:46.288 --> 00:02:48.246
I was 19.

53
00:02:48.329 --> 00:02:50.079
Was barely a man.

54
00:02:51.121 --> 00:02:53.663
Mom says never a man.

55
00:02:54.704 --> 00:02:56.829
We were both kids. so...

56
00:02:59.871 --> 00:03:03.371
Hey. This-this is... this is
really nice. talking like this.

57
00:03:03.454 --> 00:03:06.371
Yeah. if only I'd tended bar
when I was five.

58
00:03:06.454 --> 00:03:08.788
we'd be just peachy.

59
00:03:13.538 --> 00:03:14.996
How do I have
the world's slowest

60
00:03:15.079 --> 00:03:16.788
and most expensive mechanic?

61
00:03:16.871 --> 00:03:19.746
Hey.
You know. I got real good

62
00:03:19.829 --> 00:03:21.829
at f-fixing Humvees
over in Afghanistan.

63
00:03:21.913 --> 00:03:23.413
Happy to help.

64
00:03:27.788 --> 00:03:29.996
I learned long ago...

65
00:03:30.079 --> 00:03:31.621
to handle problems myself.

66
00:03:32.913 --> 00:03:35.371
I know I wasn't around
when you needed me most.

67
00:03:36.913 --> 00:03:39.121
But I'm here now. so...

68
00:03:41.579 --> 00:03:44.246
Having a bar between us...

69
00:03:44.329 --> 00:03:47.954
it feels about right... Cal.

70
00:03:58.996 --> 00:04:01.496
Drove all the way to Wyoming
for nothing.

71
00:04:03.329 --> 00:04:05.163
Horse taking a bite out
of the buyer made it worth it.

72
00:04:05.246 --> 00:04:07.496
That wasn't funny.

73
00:04:07.579 --> 00:04:09.204
Oh. yes. it was.

74
00:04:10.579 --> 00:04:12.413
I'm gonna call Travis.

75
00:04:12.496 --> 00:04:14.204
He'll find a home
for this bronc.

76
00:04:15.288 --> 00:04:17.246
Maybe keeping Mom's horse
is a sign

77
00:04:17.329 --> 00:04:18.996
you should be coming
to the remembrance ceremony

78
00:04:19.079 --> 00:04:20.496
on Broken Rock.

79
00:04:21.496 --> 00:04:23.496
We'll see.

80
00:04:30.371 --> 00:04:31.538
Hayley?

81
00:04:33.246 --> 00:04:34.246
Hayley.

82
00:04:37.538 --> 00:04:39.246
- It's Tate.
- Tate.

83
00:04:39.329 --> 00:04:40.871
Right. Um...

84
00:04:40.954 --> 00:04:42.538
What are you doing here?

85
00:04:44.121 --> 00:04:45.538
Just trying to sell a horse.

86
00:04:45.621 --> 00:04:47.038
You?

87
00:04:49.746 --> 00:04:51.579
Just out driving.

88
00:04:51.663 --> 00:04:53.454
- In Wyoming?
- My boyfriend

89
00:04:53.538 --> 00:04:55.163
likes road trips.

90
00:04:57.246 --> 00:04:58.829
Um...

91
00:04:58.913 --> 00:05:01.996
I can't keep him waiting though.
so. I'll... I'll see you.

92
00:05:13.954 --> 00:05:15.163
Who was that?

93
00:05:16.163 --> 00:05:17.788
Old classmate from the rez.

94
00:05:18.829 --> 00:05:20.829
She doesn't seem like herself.

95
00:05:23.204 --> 00:05:24.954
Strange place for a kid to be.

96
00:05:36.663 --> 00:05:38.871
How'd lunch go with Maddie?

97
00:05:38.954 --> 00:05:41.538
Scar tissue's
preventing healing. You know.

98
00:05:43.121 --> 00:05:44.871
What'd you do to annoy her?

99
00:05:44.954 --> 00:05:48.871
Besides not being
in her life since she was five?

100
00:05:48.954 --> 00:05:50.746
Well. being estranged
for 20 years.

101
00:05:50.829 --> 00:05:54.121
you can't exactly expect her to
welcome you back with open arms.

102
00:05:54.204 --> 00:05:56.788
The fact she is talking to you

103
00:05:56.871 --> 00:05:58.204
is a positive.

104
00:05:58.288 --> 00:05:59.746
Positive? Uh...

105
00:05:59.829 --> 00:06:01.788
I tried to help her out
of this jam.

106
00:06:01.871 --> 00:06:04.413
and. you know.
she just shot me down. so...

107
00:06:04.496 --> 00:06:05.746
Healing from a painful past

108
00:06:05.829 --> 00:06:08.329
doesn't come easy.

109
00:06:08.413 --> 00:06:10.996
Or that's her and I have no idea
what I'm talking about.

110
00:06:11.079 --> 00:06:12.704
Hey. Harry.

111
00:06:22.163 --> 00:06:23.871
¡Golazo!

112
00:06:23.954 --> 00:06:26.538
As always. feels like
I'm at a cultural disadvantage.

113
00:06:26.621 --> 00:06:29.496
My dad raised me on baseball.
not soccer.

114
00:06:29.579 --> 00:06:31.246
- Double or nothing?
- No way.

115
00:06:31.329 --> 00:06:32.996
I'm saving my cash
for a new place.

116
00:06:33.079 --> 00:06:34.913
How much is your rent
in Bozeman?

117
00:06:34.996 --> 00:06:37.079
Given I'm hoping
to pop smoke out of here.

118
00:06:37.163 --> 00:06:40.163
I'm on a weekly lease. but it's
a quarter of what I paid in D.C.

119
00:06:40.246 --> 00:06:41.996
You looking to leave the rez?

120
00:06:42.079 --> 00:06:43.704
More like they're looking
to evict me.

121
00:06:43.788 --> 00:06:45.704
Becoming a marshal
didn't go over so great.

122
00:06:47.329 --> 00:06:48.829
Little late. cowboy.

123
00:06:48.913 --> 00:06:51.288
Spent the night hollering
at that Dolly girl?

124
00:06:51.371 --> 00:06:52.913
Thought you were done
investigating me.

125
00:06:52.996 --> 00:06:55.954
That's not a denial.

126
00:06:56.038 --> 00:06:57.538
Hey. does it strike you as odd

127
00:06:57.621 --> 00:06:59.079
that a Broken Rock teenager

128
00:06:59.163 --> 00:07:00.746
would be wandering around
a truck stop parking lot

129
00:07:00.829 --> 00:07:01.746
in Wyoming?

130
00:07:01.829 --> 00:07:03.829
Who's the kid?

131
00:07:03.913 --> 00:07:05.121
Hayley Charlo.

132
00:07:05.204 --> 00:07:06.329
A friend of my son's.

133
00:07:07.371 --> 00:07:09.704
Mom reported her missing
right after I left tribal police

134
00:07:09.788 --> 00:07:10.996
about four months ago.

135
00:07:12.496 --> 00:07:14.663
Missing.
What. she run away?

136
00:07:15.704 --> 00:07:17.079
Nobody knows.

137
00:07:17.163 --> 00:07:18.704
That's how it goes with a lot of
these cases.

138
00:07:18.788 --> 00:07:20.496
Was she alone?

139
00:07:20.579 --> 00:07:22.704
She said she was
with her boyfriend.

140
00:07:22.788 --> 00:07:24.413
My son said she wasn't herself.

141
00:07:25.871 --> 00:07:27.538
Underage. out of sorts.

142
00:07:27.621 --> 00:07:29.663
at a truck stop
across state lines.

143
00:07:29.746 --> 00:07:31.371
Could be a victim
of trafficking.

144
00:07:32.579 --> 00:07:34.038
Sex trafficking?

145
00:07:34.121 --> 00:07:35.621
She's just a kid.

146
00:07:37.621 --> 00:07:39.621
Okay. I get a little nervous
when I walk into a room

147
00:07:39.704 --> 00:07:41.746
and it's this quiet.

148
00:07:41.829 --> 00:07:44.246
Cowboy may have stumbled
on a trafficking case.

149
00:07:44.329 --> 00:07:47.079
It's a girl
Tate went to school with.

150
00:07:47.163 --> 00:07:48.788
Tribal police have

151
00:07:48.871 --> 00:07:50.121
limited resources.

152
00:07:50.204 --> 00:07:52.079
Be nice to use ours
to dig into this.

153
00:07:52.163 --> 00:07:54.038
maybe coax 'em
into asking for assistance.

154
00:07:54.121 --> 00:07:56.246
Look. it's a worthy cause.

155
00:07:56.329 --> 00:07:59.413
y'all. but we just caught
an assignment. so...

156
00:08:00.996 --> 00:08:02.579
Sammy LaChance. A...

157
00:08:03.621 --> 00:08:05.996
...suspect
in multiple homicide cases.

158
00:08:06.079 --> 00:08:08.329
- We're going manhunting?
- Not quite.

159
00:08:08.413 --> 00:08:09.704
LaChance is a key witness

160
00:08:09.788 --> 00:08:11.663
in a big federal trial
up in Helena.

161
00:08:11.746 --> 00:08:14.163
so we're on protective duty.

162
00:08:14.246 --> 00:08:16.413
Government would rather
protect a killer

163
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.704
than lift a finger
for missing girls.

164
00:08:20.246 --> 00:08:22.079
You don't need five rifles
to go babysit.

165
00:08:22.163 --> 00:08:24.538
Why don't you let us
go talk to Hayley's mom?

166
00:08:25.538 --> 00:08:29.371
I'm certain she'd appreciate
knowing her kid's alive.

167
00:08:29.454 --> 00:08:30.954
Hey. look.

168
00:08:31.954 --> 00:08:33.788
You can relay what you saw.
but don't represent

169
00:08:33.871 --> 00:08:35.329
the badge.
Tread lightly. all right?

170
00:08:37.329 --> 00:08:39.954
Treading lightly
is Cowboy's specialty.

171
00:09:23.412 --> 00:09:25.912
Also has charges
for aggravated assault.

172
00:09:25.995 --> 00:09:29.037
loan sharking
and domestic abuse.

173
00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:30.495
A model citizen.

174
00:09:30.579 --> 00:09:32.245
What kind of witness
can this scumbag be?

175
00:09:32.329 --> 00:09:34.120
An important one. okay?

176
00:09:34.204 --> 00:09:35.995
Fed's case
hinges on his testimony.

177
00:09:36.079 --> 00:09:38.454
Must be a real monster they're
going after to cut him a deal.

178
00:09:38.537 --> 00:09:39.495
What I assumed.

179
00:09:39.579 --> 00:09:41.995
But the case is actually against

180
00:09:42.079 --> 00:09:43.579
a construction company

181
00:09:43.662 --> 00:09:45.079
charged with defrauding
the government

182
00:09:45.162 --> 00:09:48.329
out of millions
in a bid rigging scheme.

183
00:09:48.412 --> 00:09:49.745
They're cutting a killer a deal
over some couch change.

184
00:09:49.829 --> 00:09:52.204
Good idea fairies strike again.

185
00:09:52.287 --> 00:09:53.954
It's gonna be on us
to keep LaChance safe

186
00:09:54.037 --> 00:09:56.329
until his transport
to Helena arrive.

187
00:09:56.412 --> 00:09:58.745
Became a marshal
to hunt monsters.

188
00:09:58.829 --> 00:10:00.245
not protect them.

189
00:10:01.620 --> 00:10:06.079
Can we at least do something for
the girl that Kayce ran into?

190
00:10:06.162 --> 00:10:08.829
Check the truck stop?

191
00:10:12.537 --> 00:10:13.662
Okay.

192
00:10:13.745 --> 00:10:15.412
Reach out
to Wyoming State Police.

193
00:10:19.037 --> 00:10:20.537
You saw Hayley?

194
00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:22.370
Did she look like
she was eating?

195
00:10:22.454 --> 00:10:24.204
Was-was she happy?

196
00:10:25.579 --> 00:10:26.912
It's hard to say. ma'am.

197
00:10:27.912 --> 00:10:30.537
She said she was on a road trip
with her boyfriend.

198
00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:32.329
Do you know who that could be?

199
00:10:33.995 --> 00:10:35.620
Right before she disappeared.

200
00:10:35.704 --> 00:10:37.829
uh. I'd find her
all hours of the night.

201
00:10:37.912 --> 00:10:39.995
face lit up by that damn phone.

202
00:10:40.079 --> 00:10:41.662
And I'd ask her
who she was texting.

203
00:10:41.745 --> 00:10:44.370
and she'd swear
it was nobody and...

204
00:10:44.454 --> 00:10:46.287
One night. my car's gone.

205
00:10:46.370 --> 00:10:49.912
and I prayed she had gone
to stay with Chrystal. but...

206
00:10:49.995 --> 00:10:53.745
then the state troopers
found my car in Spurling.

207
00:10:53.829 --> 00:10:55.912
And-and I said.
"I don't care about my car.

208
00:10:55.995 --> 00:10:59.787
Where's my daughter?" And they...
I still don't have an answer.

209
00:11:01.329 --> 00:11:02.704
So you haven't heard
from her since?

210
00:11:02.787 --> 00:11:04.204
None of her friends have either.

211
00:11:04.287 --> 00:11:06.745
Mm. none know this guy.

212
00:11:06.829 --> 00:11:08.495
Do...

213
00:11:08.579 --> 00:11:10.454
Think she really
went off with him?

214
00:11:11.829 --> 00:11:13.829
Given what you shared.

215
00:11:13.912 --> 00:11:17.162
seems likely Hayley
met someone online

216
00:11:17.245 --> 00:11:20.829
who groomed her and then lured
her off of Broken Rock.

217
00:11:22.412 --> 00:11:24.745
Oh. it's a cruel thing
when your best hope

218
00:11:24.829 --> 00:11:27.954
is your child
fled the life you gave her.

219
00:11:28.037 --> 00:11:29.620
Ow!

220
00:11:32.370 --> 00:11:34.204
You can't blame yourself. Ellie.

221
00:11:45.787 --> 00:11:48.995
My daughter Ava went missing
just over a year ago.

222
00:11:49.995 --> 00:11:51.037
He knows.

223
00:11:53.412 --> 00:11:56.079
Worked that case till my
last day on the tribal police.

224
00:11:56.162 --> 00:11:58.329
Wish I'd been able to do more.

225
00:11:59.370 --> 00:12:00.370
I know. Miles.

226
00:12:01.370 --> 00:12:02.995
And. Kayce.
you got a fighting spirit.

227
00:12:03.079 --> 00:12:04.162
Like Monica.

228
00:12:05.412 --> 00:12:07.329
Didn't realize you knew her.

229
00:12:09.079 --> 00:12:10.954
After Ava disappeared.

230
00:12:11.037 --> 00:12:12.329
I founded North Star.

231
00:12:12.412 --> 00:12:14.787
an advocacy group
that raises awareness

232
00:12:14.870 --> 00:12:16.829
about girls missing
from the reservations.

233
00:12:16.912 --> 00:12:20.495
Chairman Rainwater allows me
to work out of his office

234
00:12:20.579 --> 00:12:21.579
to help spread this message.

235
00:12:24.370 --> 00:12:28.079
Monica was committed
to working with us before...

236
00:12:29.829 --> 00:12:31.662
I'm so sorry.

237
00:12:33.704 --> 00:12:35.412
You saw my Hayley.

238
00:12:36.454 --> 00:12:38.787
I didn't know until today
she was still alive.

239
00:12:40.454 --> 00:12:43.162
Promise me
you won't let this go.

240
00:12:51.745 --> 00:12:53.579
View from here is pretty nice.

241
00:12:54.620 --> 00:12:55.704
How's it look. hon?

242
00:12:55.787 --> 00:12:57.829
Any threats to my well-being?

243
00:12:57.912 --> 00:13:00.912
- Not from out there.
- He orders another steak.

244
00:13:00.995 --> 00:13:03.412
just keep the knives
away from me.

245
00:13:03.495 --> 00:13:05.870
Think the taxpayers
would be happy we're footing

246
00:13:05.954 --> 00:13:08.537
a suspected killer's staycation?

247
00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:10.454
Well. DOJ has their priorities.

248
00:13:10.537 --> 00:13:11.579
Yeah. but do we?

249
00:13:11.662 --> 00:13:13.037
'Cause someone's
preying on girls

250
00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:14.787
and we're luxuriating.

251
00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:19.245
Wyoming State Troopers report
no sightings of Hayley.

252
00:13:19.329 --> 00:13:21.537
Hope for luck
with the Amber Alert I issued.

253
00:13:21.620 --> 00:13:23.162
It's not our case. okay?

254
00:13:23.245 --> 00:13:24.995
So quit getting invested.

255
00:13:25.079 --> 00:13:27.204
Chance to reunite an estranged
parent with their daughter's

256
00:13:27.287 --> 00:13:29.620
not something
you're invested in?

257
00:13:31.287 --> 00:13:33.162
Security sweep. floor-to-floor.

258
00:13:57.079 --> 00:13:58.162
Coming to make
another roadblock?

259
00:13:59.162 --> 00:14:02.620
Well. marshals on the rez
makes some folks uneasy.

260
00:14:02.704 --> 00:14:04.162
Even if you lived here.

261
00:14:04.245 --> 00:14:05.954
Or still do.

262
00:14:06.037 --> 00:14:08.412
Think everyone but you and
the chairman has keyed my car.

263
00:14:08.495 --> 00:14:10.204
Mm.

264
00:14:10.287 --> 00:14:11.912
Sera reached out.

265
00:14:11.995 --> 00:14:13.412
shared you saw our Hayley.

266
00:14:13.495 --> 00:14:15.037
I figured
Ellie would want to know

267
00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:16.829
that her daughter
was still alive.

268
00:14:16.912 --> 00:14:18.662
Of course.

269
00:14:18.745 --> 00:14:21.579
But understand
what you've done here today.

270
00:14:21.662 --> 00:14:25.370
You've given Ellie something she
didn't have a few minutes ago.

271
00:14:25.454 --> 00:14:26.704
Hope.

272
00:14:26.787 --> 00:14:28.329
Is that a bad thing?

273
00:14:28.412 --> 00:14:31.412
Around here. hope is a knife
that cuts two ways.

274
00:14:31.495 --> 00:14:33.662
And since nobody has reached out

275
00:14:33.745 --> 00:14:35.079
to the tribal police.

276
00:14:35.162 --> 00:14:38.162
you're here
in an unofficial capacity.

277
00:14:38.245 --> 00:14:41.329
meaning you're spreading
false hope.

278
00:14:41.412 --> 00:14:43.412
If tribal police
ask for assistance.

279
00:14:43.495 --> 00:14:45.245
we could help.

280
00:14:45.329 --> 00:14:48.120
Those requests have fallen
on deaf ears many times before.

281
00:14:49.162 --> 00:14:50.495
Local. state.

282
00:14:50.579 --> 00:14:52.704
federal authorities
were all too happy

283
00:14:52.787 --> 00:14:56.370
to declare our missing girls
runaways.

284
00:14:56.454 --> 00:14:58.245
Maybe we can change that.

285
00:14:58.329 --> 00:15:02.204
We've walked a similar path
on this land before. Kayce.

286
00:15:02.287 --> 00:15:03.870
Searching for a missing girl.

287
00:15:05.912 --> 00:15:07.287
The search ended quickly.

288
00:15:07.370 --> 00:15:08.995
And tragically.

289
00:15:09.079 --> 00:15:10.995
Listen. this evil
keeps evolving.

290
00:15:11.079 --> 00:15:14.620
but the results stay the same.

291
00:15:14.704 --> 00:15:16.287
And for the families.

292
00:15:16.370 --> 00:15:17.870
the wounds never heal.

293
00:15:18.912 --> 00:15:20.162
Could be different this time.

294
00:15:21.162 --> 00:15:23.120
Well. we all know
the chances of that.

295
00:15:34.454 --> 00:15:37.370
Our missing daughters could use
a sheepdog like Kayce.

296
00:15:37.454 --> 00:15:39.787
His superiors
would never allow it.

297
00:15:39.870 --> 00:15:42.245
Yet another battle
we fight alone.

298
00:15:44.204 --> 00:15:47.745
How can we fight it when we're
not allowed on the battlefield?

299
00:16:01.787 --> 00:16:04.870
Miles says Hayley and
another Broken Rock girl. Ava.

300
00:16:04.954 --> 00:16:07.079
were both targeted online.

301
00:16:07.162 --> 00:16:10.245
No wonder Miles is so dialed in.

302
00:16:10.329 --> 00:16:13.745
Guarantee he and Kayce have
found a few trees to bark up.

303
00:16:13.829 --> 00:16:16.704
Can't hurt for us to do
some moonlighting of our own.

304
00:16:16.787 --> 00:16:18.495
A look into Hayley
and Ava's social media

305
00:16:18.579 --> 00:16:19.579
could shed some light.

306
00:16:19.662 --> 00:16:20.704
Okay. Yeah.

307
00:16:24.537 --> 00:16:27.204
No suspicious activity
or persons out there.

308
00:16:27.287 --> 00:16:28.704
Hotel's quiet.

309
00:16:28.787 --> 00:16:30.620
- Good.
- Peaceful.

310
00:16:30.704 --> 00:16:32.245
I like that.

311
00:16:32.329 --> 00:16:34.829
It's why I'm hoping
I'm getting relocated to Hawaii.

312
00:16:34.912 --> 00:16:36.787
Maybe California.

313
00:16:36.870 --> 00:16:38.870
Just nowhere cold.

314
00:16:38.954 --> 00:16:42.079
Relocated?
You're going into WITSEC?

315
00:16:42.162 --> 00:16:43.870
All I got to do
is squeal in court later.

316
00:16:43.954 --> 00:16:46.204
then tomorrow's
the first day of my new life.

317
00:16:46.287 --> 00:16:47.829
- Clean slate.
- Lot of money

318
00:16:47.912 --> 00:16:51.579
and resources are going
into burying your sins.

319
00:16:53.787 --> 00:16:55.495
Who could be more deserving?

320
00:16:55.579 --> 00:16:56.745
Hey. escort's en route.

321
00:16:56.829 --> 00:16:57.745
Let's go.
Let's get you presentable

322
00:16:57.829 --> 00:16:58.829
for the courtroom.

323
00:17:08.204 --> 00:17:11.120
I got into Hayley
and Ava's social media.

324
00:17:11.204 --> 00:17:12.620
Looks like they both interacted
with someone

325
00:17:12.704 --> 00:17:14.954
who calls himself
"green_eyezz44."

326
00:17:16.995 --> 00:17:20.579
Thirst trap for girls
who want to escape.

327
00:17:20.662 --> 00:17:23.870
Engages them. lures them
off the reservation.

328
00:17:23.954 --> 00:17:25.995
then puts them
in compromising positions

329
00:17:26.079 --> 00:17:27.870
he can blackmail them with.

330
00:17:28.912 --> 00:17:30.454
I wish I could
get an ID on this sicko.

331
00:17:30.537 --> 00:17:32.954
but the app only requires
a first name to sign up.

332
00:17:33.037 --> 00:17:34.579
He used "Noah."

333
00:17:34.662 --> 00:17:37.579
Still. the hats and shades
make FRS a waste of time.

334
00:17:37.662 --> 00:17:39.912
Uh. trace an IP address.

335
00:17:41.995 --> 00:17:43.995
It's masked by a VPN.

336
00:17:45.954 --> 00:17:48.995
Wait.
He just posted.

337
00:17:49.079 --> 00:17:53.204
This guy is literally
on the prowl right now.

338
00:17:58.995 --> 00:18:01.954
You never mentioned
you worked Ava's case.

339
00:18:02.037 --> 00:18:05.287
Another instance of something
I started but couldn't finish.

340
00:18:05.370 --> 00:18:08.412
Lot of open wounds
on Broken Rock.

341
00:18:09.454 --> 00:18:11.620
Be nice to track down
Hayley and Ava.

342
00:18:11.704 --> 00:18:13.245
heal at least a couple.

343
00:18:14.245 --> 00:18:16.787
Could help my standing
in the community.

344
00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:19.245
I'm not too comfortable here
myself.

345
00:18:19.329 --> 00:18:21.245
Bad memories?

346
00:18:23.412 --> 00:18:24.870
Some of my best.

347
00:18:30.704 --> 00:18:32.037
Andrea just got a hit on a guy

348
00:18:32.120 --> 00:18:33.954
who was DMing
both Ava and Hayley.

349
00:18:34.037 --> 00:18:35.745
That could be our predator.

350
00:18:35.829 --> 00:18:37.954
He's active.
hunting for his next victim.

351
00:18:38.954 --> 00:18:40.579
That's Greely Creek.

352
00:18:40.662 --> 00:18:42.662
I used to take Tate
to that hole.

353
00:18:43.745 --> 00:18:45.037
This was posted a half hour ago.

354
00:18:46.037 --> 00:18:47.245
You up for some fishing?

355
00:18:53.954 --> 00:18:55.579
Dirtbag isn't walking
into his new life.

356
00:18:55.662 --> 00:18:58.454
- He's taking a motorcade.
- Feels more and more like

357
00:18:58.537 --> 00:19:00.162
the worst of us get rewarded

358
00:19:00.245 --> 00:19:03.412
while the most vulnerable
just keep getting stepped on.

359
00:19:07.370 --> 00:19:09.245
LaChance is still getting ready.

360
00:19:13.412 --> 00:19:14.912
If we can't help
the most vulnerable.

361
00:19:14.995 --> 00:19:17.620
